#
# Git LFS routing — PER-REPO template (NOT a global attributes file).
#
# Copy this into the root of a repository (or into a subdirectory you own inside
# a shared monorepo) as `.gitattributes`, then commit it:  git lfs-init
#
# Why per-repo and not global: a global filter=lfs rule applies inside every
# submodule and every coworker's directory, rewriting binaries you don't own
# into LFS pointers. Committing the routing to the specific tree you own keeps
# LFS scoped to that tree, versioned, and reproducible on fresh clones.
#
# Every binary class routes through Git LFS (filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text)
# so it is stored as a pointer, never a raw blob; LFS passes already-committed
# non-pointer blobs through unchanged on checkout, so adopting this is safe for
# existing repos and only affects future adds.
#
# NOTE: git does NOT support inline/trailing comments in .gitattributes — a `#`
# mid-line is parsed as a bogus attribute and corrupts the rule. Every comment
# here is therefore on its own line, above the rule it describes.
#

#
# Images — raster photos/graphics, plus vector and editor project files.
#
# Portable Network Graphics
*.png filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
# JPEG image
*.jpg filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
# JPEG image
*.jpeg filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
# Graphics Interchange Format image
*.gif filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
# Windows bitmap image
*.bmp filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
# Tagged Image File Format image
*.tiff filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
# Icon image
*.ico filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
# WebP image
*.webp filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
# AV1 Image File Format
*.avif filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
# High Efficiency Image Container (Apple)
*.heic filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
# Adobe Photoshop document
*.psd filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
# Adobe Illustrator document
*.ai filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
# Encapsulated PostScript vector image
*.eps filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text

